    "long_instructions": "### Building Effects\r\n\r\n**Define:** You've been asked to design a song that builds toward a big musical moment, like the drop in a dance track or the chorus in a power ballad. You'll need to combine effects, track lengths, and timing to shape how your song grows and surprises the listener.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Pick a moment in your song that you want to build toward - which tracks will start the song quietly or slowly? Where should you place rest blocks to create contrast or surprise? Listen to the example below for what this could sound like!\r\n\r\n**Try:** Code your song to create a build-up. Try different combinations of effects and rests to shape the energy of your song.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Listen to your song and iterate until it sounds the way you want it to. In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- At least 3 effect blocks\r\n- Tracks with different lengths\r\n- Tracks that are offset using rest blocks",
